EHe%20said%20that%20the%20carrier%20is%20phasing%20out%20its%20Embraer%20fleet%2C%20noting%20that%20consolidating%20maintenance%20and%20crew%20members%20into%20one%20aircraft%20type%20will%20simplify%20the%20business%20and%20lower%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpirit%20and%20Frontier%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-spirit-southwest-jetblue-struggle-profit-scrambling-changes-tickets-seats-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etried%20to%20lure%20customers%20away%20from%20mainline%3C%2Fa%3E%20American%20Airlines%2C%20Delta%20Air%20Lines%2C%20and%20United%20Airlines%20by%20offering%20cheap%20tickets%20at%20major%20airports%20in%20places%20like%20New%20York%2C%20California%2C%20and%20the%20Southeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20earnings%20call%20this%20month%2C%20United%20CEO%20Scott%20Kirby%20said%20he%20doesn't%20%26quot%3Bsee%20how%20it's%20possible%26quot%3B%20for%20low-cost%20carriers%20to%20profitably%20fly%20to%20larger%20airports%20because%20governments%20have%20%26quot%3Bpriced%20low-cost%20carriers%20out%20of%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fees%20to%20fly%20into%20large%20cities%20are%20high%2C%20but%20budget%20carriers%20are%20also%20impacted%20by%20congestion%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20longer%20taxi%20times.%20This%20makes%20turning%20planes%20around%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20keystones%20of%20a%20budget%20business%20model%20%E2%80%94%20much%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStruggling%20to%20stay%20afloat%20in%20these%20expensive%2C%20oversaturated%20airports%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspirit-airlines-chapter-11-bankruptcy-budget-airline-tickets-baggage-issues-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpirit%20and%20Frontier%20have%20adjusted%20their%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cut%20dozens%20of%20routes%2C%20slashed%20capacity%20by%20flying%20fewer%20planes%2C%20and%20withdrawn%20from%20some%20markets.%3C%2F